39_semi-log_get_base


  1. Question

    An exponential growth curve, \(y=B^x\) with base \(B>1\), is graphed below using a semi-log plot.


    Based on the red point, estimate the base \(B\).


    Solution

    Determine the coordinates of the point on the graph.


    We know that \(B^{2.2}=7\). To solve for \(B\), raise both sides of the equation to the power of \(\frac{1}{2.2}\).

    \[\left(B^{2.2}\right)^{\frac{1}{2.2}}=\left(7\right)^{\frac{1}{2.2}}\]

    We know from our exponent rules that \((a^x)^y\equiv a^{xy}\). We also know that \(c\cdot \frac{1}{c}=1\) for any \(c\ne 0\). Those two rules allow us to simplify the left side.

    \[B~=~\left(7\right)^{\frac{1}{2.2}}\]

    Use a calculator.

    \[B~\approx~2.4217844\]
